  "text": "The temperature scenarios in this study are based on the ECHAM4/OPYC3 AOGCM with the transient GSDIO integration [CITATION_1] , which includes greenhouse gases, tropospheric ozone, and direct as well as indirect sulphur aerosol forcing. In this integration, the concentrations of greenhouse gases have been specified according to the IPCC IS92a scenario. Compared to IPCCs new set of emission scenarios (SRES) (IPCC, 2001: 532) , the projected increase in the global mean temperature up to 2050 for the IS92a scenario is similar to SRES B1, and lower than for the other SRES scenarios.",
